{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "There are singledomain Text-to-SQL datasets such as GeoQuery (ZELLE; MOONEY, 1996), ATIS (DAHL et al., 1994), Restaurant (IYER et al., 2017) and SQL-Eval (PING, 2023), which are designed for specific information retrieval tasks.",
    "WikiSQL (ZHONG; XIONG; SOCHER, 2017) has 80,654 NL sentences and SQL annotations of 24,241 tables.",
    "Each query in WikiSQL is limited to the same table and does not contain complex operations such as sorting and grouping.",
    "The Spider -Yale Semantic Parsing and Text-to-SQL Challenge (YU et al., 2018b) offers datasets for training and testing Text-to-SQL tools.",
    "Spider features nearly 200 databases covering 138 different domains from three resources: 70 complex databases from different college database courses, SQL tutorial websites, online CSV files, and textbook examples; 40 databases from DatabaseAnswers; foot_1 and 90 databases based on WikiSQL, with about 500 tables in about 90 different domains."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "There are singledomain Text-to-SQL datasets such as GeoQuery (ZELLE; MOONEY, 1996), ATIS (DAHL et al., 1994), Restaurant (IYER et al., 2017) and SQL-Eval (PING, 2023), which are designed for specific information retrieval tasks.",
    "The Spider -Yale Semantic Parsing and Text-to-SQL Challenge (YU et al., 2018b) offers datasets for training and testing Text-to-SQL tools."
  ]
